def: The reverse, or left-hand, page of a book or a folded sheet ofpaper; -- opposed to recto.
One who goes on an excursion, or pleasure trip.
One who is recidivous or is characterized by recidivism; anincorrigible criminal. -- Re*cid`i*vis"tic (#), a.
To separate the strands of; to undo, as a braid; to unravel; todisentangle.
The quality or state of being cragged; cragginess.
A denier or opponent of Christ. Specif.: A great antagonist,person or power, expected to precede Christ's second coming.
A fossil echinus of the genus Cannulus; -- so called from itssupposed resemblance to a cap.
